Class AccessControl2Queues

  • java.lang.Object
    • jmarkov.MarkovProcess<S,E>
      • jmarkov.SimpleMarkovProcess<examples.jmarkov.AccessControl2QueuesState,examples.jmarkov.AccessControl2QueuesEvent>
        • examples.jmarkov.AccessControl2Queues
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JMarkovElement

    public class AccessControl2Queues
extends SimpleMarkovProcess<examples.jmarkov.AccessControl2QueuesState,examples.jmarkov.AccessControl2QueuesEvent>
    This class represents a network with 2 queues in tandem, where the second queue has a buffer of size B and the first has a unit buffer.
    Author:
    Daniel F. Silva (2011)

                    int[] length)
        General constructor.
        Parameters:
        B - Buffer Size
        Mu1 - First Server Rate.
        Mu2 - Second Server Rate.
        L - Arrival Rate.
        c1 - Cost of turning away.
        c2 - Cost of lost customer.
        pol - Policy (true is greedy, false is prudent)
